# Azure Naming Convention

## Resource Naming Format

1. General Format
 
  ``` txt
  Format: [resource_type]-[app_name][purpose]-[cloud_provider]-[region_code]-[env]-[running_number]
          [resource_type][app_name][purpose][cloud_provider][region_code][env][running_number]
  
  Field Descriptions:
    Resource Type       ==> "Azure Recommended Abbreviations"
    Application Name    ==> free text without hyphens and doesn't violate "Azure naming restriction"
    Purpose (optional)  ==> free text without hyphens and doesn't violate "Azure naming restriction"
    Cloud Provider      ==> az (Azure) | aw (AWS) | gc (GCP)
    Region Code         ==> asse (southeastasia) | asea (eastasia)
    Environment         ==> dev | sit | uat | stg | prd | sbx
    Running Number      ==> 001 | 002 | 003 | ...

  Example:
    resource group     ==> rg-abcd-az-asse-prd-001
    virtual network    ==> vnet-abcd-az-asse-prd-001
    subnet             ==> snet-abcd-az-asse-prd-001
    key vault          ==> kvabcdazasseprd001
    api management     ==> apimabcdazasseprd001
    container registry ==> acrabcdazasseprd001
  ```

  References:
  - [Azure naming restriction](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-resource-manager/management/resource-name-rules)
  - [Azure Recommended Abbreviations](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cloud-adoption-framework/ready/azure-best-practices/resource-abbreviations)
  - [Azure Regions to 4-letter abbreviations and numberic codes](#appendix1)
 
2. Window VM format (Due to hostname of Window VM is limited to 15 characters)

  ``` txt
  Format: [env][app_name][cloud_provider_code][region_code][resource_type][running_number]
  
  Field Descriptions:
      Resource Type       ==> vm | vmss
      Application Name    ==> 7 charaters (vm) | 5 charaters (vmss)
      Purpose (optional)  ==> share character space with "Application Name"
      Cloud Provider Code ==> 1 (az) | 2 (aws) | 3 (gcp) | 4 (huawei) | etc
      Region Code         ==> 01 (southeastasia) | 02 (eastasia) | etc
      Environment         ==> d (dev) | i (sit) | u (uat) | s (stg) | p (prd) | b (sandbox)
      Running Number      ==> 01 | 02 | 03 | ...

  Example:
      vmabcdsdb101p01
      vmabcdsdb101p02
      vmabcdssa101p01
      vmabcdssa101p02
  ```

  References:
  - [Azure Regions to 4-letter abbreviations and numberic codes](#appendix1)

## Example

### Management Group
 
- **Restrictions**:
  - length: 1-64
  - regex: `^[a-zA-Z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9\-\._]+[a-zA-Z0-9]$`
- **Example**:
  - mg-abcdef
  - mg-abcdef-dev
  - mg-abcdef-prd

### Subscription

- **Restrictions**:
  - length: 1-64
  - regex: `^[a-zA-Z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9-._]+[a-zA-Z0-9_]$`
- **Example**:
  - sub-Affiliate-az-prd
  - sub-AIChatbotExternal-az-dev
  - sub-AICallCenter-az-sbx

### Private DNS Virtual Network Link

- **Restrictions**:
  - length: 1-80
  - regex: `^[a-zA-Z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9-._]+[a-zA-Z0-9_]$`
- **Example**:
    - link-vnet-abcdef-az-asse-prd-001
    - link-vnet-abcdef-az-asse-prd-002

### Virtual Network Peering

- **Restrictions**:
  - length: 1-80
  - regex: `^[a-zA-Z0-9][a-zA-Z0-9-._]+[a-zA-Z0-9_]$`
- **Example**:
  - vpeer-vnet-source-az-asse-prd-001-vnet-remote-az-asse-prd-001
  - vpeer-vnet-source-az-asse-prd-002-vnet-remote-az-asse-prd-002

